column5: 5 here.LOL
the old saying guys. its better to give then receive lol. .sorry lew it was supposed to bypass the musky fishermen.
If it helps to raise the great lakes water level 3',keeper coming,lol.

man I love winter but this year it can GTH ! Weather's been so schizo this year: cold, mild, melting, cold, etc etc. now this stuff. thank god our mayor hasn't called in the forces yet lol. guess we're lucky it fell on a friday so most can leave the heavy lifting till saturday.  I'll be happy if there's this much in Algonquin if I head up for the family day long one.
Just got in for a good rip on the bravo!  With what we had before, and now this!  What a workout.  Tons of powder to play in!  Packing down the neighbours trails to they can cross country ski.

Well being in Toronto, I pushed 4 people that were stuck on my way to work and 3 on my way home... The best was a girl in a bmw with summer tires. I told her when she gets going don't let off the gas just keep it going and she can make it. Well I pushed and got her going and she was chugging up the hill. I got back in the jeep and passed her right as she got stuck again. I couldn't help but smile and wave as I drove by her. She was probably better off stuck in a snow bank anyway

Debating if I should go to work or not. All season tires but our road still isn't plowed yet. I do like money but I also like my life, and going into the bar for what could be 2 customers isn't worth it.

Glad to see you guys are getting some winter weather finally. enjoy some sledding,  For those of you who had traded in your snowblowers for a set of golf clubs, Buffalo Joe will fly a plane full  of Toros down but he can be pricey
Just sitting in the cosy warmth with fresh baked cookies and hot cocoa, and larfing at everyone else
Cookies and cocoa sounds pretty good!!   Can you send some of that tasty stuff up here?
Sorry, My wee pup just doesn't quite make the grade as a St Bernard
Perfect night for tying streamers though. All peaceful and quiet, and the Mrs is resting comfortably
That is some funny stuff!...thanks Bigugli.  Snowed all day here in the capital...talked to my attorneys...they're not calling in the military.
ahem,10 cm here.LOL
just thought we would send you torontites,,,,some fresh new white stuff. ENJOY
Just finished plowing my and my neighbors driveways, about 15 cm and it is still coming. Joys of country living.
Coming down here in Barrie like crazy, going to have to get out with the snowblower more then a few times in the next 24hrs me thinks.
It's going to take multiple shovelings here in Hamilton as well. First one done.
Well, you sent it too far George cause were getting clobbered way over here too  Just finished 2 hours with the snowblower and it looks like it's time to start all over again.

I think here in the east end of Barrie,were close to 12" already!.Will be hard walking this weekend. Some of the atv's will probably have a hard time!.Finding a beaten path will probably our best friend this weekend.
Really? Only 12" in Barrie?! We have like 2 ft and still piling!
Close to 24" in Brighton and still coming down... Going to be a BRUTAL ride in to work tonight...

Just got in from an hour in the driveway.  What are the odds.  Only the second time ever I have had to use the electric start on the blower.  She wouldn't start with the pull chord.  Must have been playing dead!  A solid 12" + in Orr lake.  Got stuck in the driveway and had to blow myself out.
Just finished plowing my commercial lots. 7 in total Took me 8 hrs and all I did was make path ways and clean the entrances. Close to 14"s here in niagara and still coming
Now go over to  Mikes and play on the sled. Thats what he,ll be doing when he gets home.LOL  Now this is winter
Just took the sled for a rip myself.Lots of thumbs up from people digging out here in Richmont Hill.
Most people didn't seem to mind this snowfall,more of a"it's about time we had a good snowfall". lol. I agree as well.  .
I cleaned a good 2ft from my driveway and it's still coming, lol!   No complaints though, I love snowy winters.   Will keep a lot of guys off the lake tomorrow!
I hope not,I would like a beaten path for Sunday.LOL
Brian, follow the snowmobile tracks, lol!
LOL Bill. I,ll PM you where I want to go,and you can make my trail.LOL

Dang I'm doing like outlaw we all put our leaf blowers (no not the guy sitting on the grass) on full throttle to keep the white stuff heading east. We have a couple inches here. Since I moved down this way 14 or so years ago I have learned to love snowless winters.
Got about 16 inches in Innisfil, and more coming down
Time to clean my driveway again, then my grandmas again, then go to work. ugh......
Checked the top of the barbecue,15" and still going!
Paul.yer allowed to do that? How was the fish,n LOL Good on ya.
Was just checking out some traffic cams in the GTA.
You still miss that Dave? lol.
Not one bit!!!! I like to watch others suffer!!!!! My 2km commute is fine by me.
